                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/597: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-06T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 6, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 6—3:12 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1095. My 1084 [<hi rend="italic">1093</hi>], December 5, 7 p.m. Following from
                    American Consul in charge at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“December 5, 10 p.m. My telegram of December 5, 11 a.m. Reliably informed
                            that discussions concerning Emshanoff, Eismont were continued today. The
                            Marshal eventually acquiesced in their appointment to other positions. A
                            reply to Litvinoff’s telegram of November 27th<note n="74"
                                xml:id="d343fn74">See telegram No. 1054, November 29, from the
                                Chargé in China, <ref target="#pg_362">p. 362</ref>.</note> in this
                            sense was sent today. Apparently no message was sent last night. Lu
                            Jung-huan has not signed [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>]; Mukden has now
                            agreed to the conditions of Soviet for starting negotiations.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
